South Korean Institute of Progressive Movement Founded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- An inaugural meeting of the  South Korean Institute of Progressive Movement was reportedly held at the Christian Hall in Seoul on March 5.
 The declaration issued at the meeting, outlining the purport of its inauguration, says: Judicious idea and theory are necessary for the victory of the democratic movement of the nation in the 21st century and the institute is founded in response to this demand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It set out tasks for the days to come, stating that the institute will do away with deviations in the past movement for independence, democracy and reunification and launch into advanced ideological and theoretical activities rooted in the realities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Public figures in their speeches said it was high time all the Koreans turned out in the struggle to defend the dignity and sovereignty of the nation under the banner of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and our nation-first spirit. The institute should put forward an action program in time in response to diverse demands of all social strata, they emphasized. 
 The meeting was followed by a commemorative seminar on the subject "The orientation of political activities in the June 15 era".

Relocation of U.S. Forces in South Korea Denounced in India 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee of the Revolutionary Socialist Party of India on March 4 published a statement denouncing the relocation of the U.S. forces in south Korea.
 Noting that the current situation of the Korean peninsula is getting more strained after the Bush administration came on the scene, the statement says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The occupation of south Korea by the U.S. forces is the root cause of all the misfortunes and sufferings of the Korean people. More than 40,000 American soldiers are constantly present in south Korea with at least 1,000 pieces of nuclear weapons and military hardware of latest types are now continuously being shipped there   In relocating its forces in south Korea the United States seeks to hasten preparations for a new war on the Korean peninsula and establish its rule over the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We bitterly condemn this scheme of the U.S. and demand that it pull its forces at once out of south Korea to allow the Korean nation to achieve the reunification of the country by itself in accordance with the main spirit of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We are certain that the friendly Korean people will firmly defend the sovereignty and dignity of their country under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il.

KCNA on U.S. Foolish Way of Thinking 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- A rumor is afloat on the international arena that the DPRK is driving the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. to a quagmire in the hope that if Bush is voted down, it would be possible to settle the nuclear issue more favorably.
 The Washington Times on March 6 in an article titled "North Korea hopes Bush to resign" said that north Korea is hoping President Bush from the Republican Party to fail in the U.S. presidential election slated for November and step down. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We do not care where such opinion came from. But we cannot but clarify that this is nothing but sheer misinformation as it is an expression of utter ignorance of the independent nature of the DPRK's diplomacy. It is clear that this misinformation is aimed to serve the purpose of speaking for the present U.S. administration which finds itself in a difficult position after being bitterly censured at home and abroad for driving the DPRK-U.S. relations to the lowest ebb and coming out to the second round of the six-way talks without any proposal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As well known to everyone, the second round of the six-way talks could not produce any positive results owing to the unreasonable attitude of the U.S. toward dialogue. It proved fruitless not because of "expectation" of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the talks we showed the greatest magnanimity, clarifying our will to scrap its nuclear program according to the proposal for a simultaneous package solution aimed to denuclearize the Korean peninsula and advancing a fair and flexible proposal for implementing the first-phase actions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, the U.S. did not show even an iota of its will to withdraw its hostile policy toward the DPRK and coexist with it in peace, obstinately insisting on the DPRK's completely scrapping its nuclear program in a verifiable and irreversible manner. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recent talks were put in a stalemate by such unreasonable attitude of the U.S. as it unilaterally insisted on the DPRK's dropping its nuclear program first. The deadlock was not attributable to the "delaying tactics" allegedly employed by DPRK in anticipation of "Bush's resignation" as claimed by the media. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such being a hard fact, some media talk about the DPRK's hope for "Bush's defeat" in the election, skeptical about the fair attitude of the DPRK toward dialogue. This can not be interpreted otherwise than an expression of ignorance of the DPRK's independent foreign policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK does not care at all whether a candidate from the Democratic Party is elected or a candidate from the Republican Party is elected in the United States because it is a matter to be decided by the U.S. voters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a foolish way of thinking to guess that the DPRK seems to be inconsistent in implementing its foreign policy in anticipation of the outcome of the U.S. presidential election. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a basic principle governing the activities of the DPRK government to firmly maintain independence in its external relations, act according to its faith and independently settle all the problems raised. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK's diplomacy is not aimed to please anyone but fair and aboveboard one that to meet its state interests. It is the diplomacy based on the principle of independence, unlike the diplomacy of those countries reading other's face devoid of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK's stand is, therefore, consistent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Whoever elected U.S. president should be willing to make a switchover in its policy toward the DPRK, drop the hostile policy toward it and express readiness to coexist with it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is a main point. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. makes a switchover in its policy toward the DPRK, though belatedly, progress will be made in the settlement of the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S.

Declaration on General Election Published in South Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- The Headquarters of the General Election Movement for the Judgment of the Outdated Politics on Behalf of the June 15 Era reportedly made public a declaration titled "Let us reshape National Assembly through political shake-up and reform" on March 6.
 The declaration charged that corrupt politics and behavior of the 16th-term "National Assembly" evoked resentment and disappointment among the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 17th-term "general election" will be a big battle between all the people aspiring after political reform and democracy and the corrupt political forces keen on maintaining their power, between the old and the new and between patriotism and treachery, the declaration said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the political shake-up and reform are an irresistible demand of the times, it said that the organization together with all the people desirous of new era and new politics declared a long march for the political reform. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underscoring the need to make the 17th-term "National Assembly" a true democratic one through the "general election", it called on all the people to turn out to the struggle to totally abolish the obsolete politics of the old times and to bring about an era of new politics.

GNP's Crimes under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- The Information Department of the Central Committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea (NDFSK) in a statement  on March 9 condemned before the whole world the crimes committed by the Grand National Party of south Korea.
The statement cited concrete facts to lay bare the GNP's pro-U.S. acts of treachery, criminal acts against national reunification, corruption, its responsibility for the deteriorated people's living and economic bankruptcy.  The history of this traitorous party is recorded with its evil acts against the nation, reunification and people, the statement noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP's pro-U.S. traitorous acts have reached their height since traitor Choe Pyong Ryol became its representative. After taking this office, he let loose a string of reckless remarks slandering the people's righteous anti-U.S. struggle for independence against colonial enslavement as a "perfidy to the U.S." and "a rash act to bedevil the south Korea-U.S. ties". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the U.S. raised a brigandish demand for the use of land as regards the transfer of its military base, the Choe Pyong Ryol group took the lead in pressurizing the "government" to accept the U.S. forces' request. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  No sooner had the U.S. started putting pressure on south Korea to dispatch its troops to Iraq than he visited his master before anyone else and promised to take the lead in making the troop dispatch successful   The GNP, pro-U.S. acts and confrontation with the north being means of its existence, has worked hard to bring the June 15 era of reunification back to the bygone era of confrontation, pursuant to the U.S. policy for Korea's permanent division. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP was opposed to the historic Pyongyang meeting. It has, therefore, desperately worked to hold in check the seventy million Koreans' dynamic grand march for independence and reunification to implement the June 15 joint declaration. The GNP cooked up "the law on special inspection of remittance to the north" not only throwing behind bars those pro-reunification patriots who contributed to the south-north reconciliation and cooperation but driving them to tragic death. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was none other than the GNP that forced the authorities to brand the north as the "principal enemy" and "the target of liquidation" and register them in the "white paper on national defence." It vociferously cried that it would not rule out even a war, zealously supporting the U.S. arms build-up and war exercises to invade the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP is a kingpin of mafia as it has met its own selfish interests by squeezing "election funds" amounting to hundreds of billions of won by the most base and despicable methods and a headquarters of corrupt political forces that resorted to arbitrary and high-handed practices, made a mockery of the people and threw the political situation into confusion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It is the GNP that has administered the money-manipulated politics, bought the post of "National Assemblyman" and won its supporters by use of money. This group of thieves called "rich grand party" extracted money running into astronomical figures from 100 businesses by fraud and swindle, threat and blackmail and a conspiratorial plot reminiscent of a detective film during the last election, the money collected from the people as taxes. It has put the "National Assembly" in a state of indefinite malfunction, shelving the problem of people's living and 1,200 other pending issues. The sharks of the GNP, taking advantage of their dominance in the NA, have turned it into a "crime-ridden assembly," "vegetable assembly," "bullet-proof assembly" and "assembly for war" in utter disregard of the people's living, their mindset and the country's economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is impossible to get rid of the people's misfortune and stop the cycle of evils of political and economic catastrophe and bring about a bright prospect of national reconciliation, unity and reunification as long as the GNP is still at large. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Now is the time to totally eliminate the GNP from the political arena and put an end to its base existence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement called upon the people from all walks of life to cut off the windpipe of the GNP and reduce it to ashes, holding aloft "Let's bury the GNP, a south Korean branch of the U.S. Republican Party and a henchman of Bush!," "Let's blow up the GNP, a modern brand Nazi party!" and other slogans.

East Sea of Korea Is Not Sea of Japan 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- The Korean people have settled on the Korean peninsula and in its surrounding areas from the cradle of human civilization. They have conquered the seas, calling the sea east of the peninsula the Korean Sea or East Sea.
 The term "East Sea" was mentioned in several hundred times in such old documents of Korea as The Chronicles of the Three States, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Heritage of the Three States, The History of Koryo Dynasty and The True Records of the Ri Dynasty. It was written as East Sea in the maps--General Map of Eight Provinces (1463), The Northwest Genealogy and The General Map of Our Country (1700) and The Grand World Map (in the latter half of 18th century). All these prove that the sea has been called Korean Sea and East Sea from centuries ago. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the recently discovered maps compiled in 18th century and later name the sea east of Korea Korean Sea, which had been widely used by Russia, Britain, France, the United States and other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sea between the Korean peninsula and Japanese Islands are written even in the maps and books printed in Japan such as The Whole Map of Asia (1794), The Sketch Map of Japanese Coastal Seas (1809), the New World Map (1810), A Picture of Four Guardians of Great Japan and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nonetheless, Japan asserts that it has inscribed the sea east of Korea as the "Japanese Sea" historically. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The distorted assertion of Japan is a new intolerable crime plus its past crimes. It only gives rise to great indignation of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jong Chang Gyu, director of the History Institute under the Academy of Social Sciences, said in an interview with KCNA that the Japanese reactionaries heated with wild ambition for overseas aggression persist in asserting that the East Sea of Korea is "Japanese sea", far from repenting and compensating for its crimes committed against the Korean nation in the past. The historically fixed names of geographical objects cannot be distorted or changed according someone's wild insistence or demand.

Dismantlement of U.S. Forces Bases in S. Korea Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists are stepping up the preparations for transferring the U.S. military bases and troops in areas north of the River Han to areas south of the river according to an "innovative military program" which calls for rendering the north's combat capacity ineffective from the outset of the war through precision attacks on it mainly by naval and air forces.
 A signed commentary of Rodong Sinmun Thursday terms this move a prelude to a war of aggression against the DPRK, a product of a criminal plot to prevent the north and the south of Korea from achieving reconciliation and cooperation and bring the holocaust of a nuclear war to the Korean nation at any cost and a dangerous move to invade Asia-Pacific and put the region under its domination. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an important issue related to the sovereignty of the Korean nation and the peace of the country and, furthermore, peace and stability in Asia-Pacific and other parts of the world to force the U.S. troops to withdraw from south Korea and dismantle their
bases there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists, prompted by their strategic and wild ambition, occupied half of the Korean peninsula, a region of geopolitical importance, and converted it into a huge military base for the three services of their forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A new war on the Korean peninsula and in Asia is unavoidable as long as the U.S. forces bases remain in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is as clear as noonday that in case a new war breaks out in Korea by the U.S. imperialists, it will not be limited to the Korean peninsula but spill over into all other areas of Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should drop its anachronistic ambition for world supremacy and make a bold decision to abolish its forces bases in south Korea and withdraw aggression troops from there as required by the Korean nation and the world peace-loving people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This would be beneficial to the U.S., too.

Front of Anti-Imperialism and Military Affairs, Main Front of Songun Revolution
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- The front of anti-imperialism and military affairs is the main front of the Songun revolution and the first life-line of the Korean revolution, its primary task being to build a powerful military force to decisively overpower the high-handed saber-rattling of the imperialists, states Rodong Sinmun today.
 The author of the article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the main front of the revolution because it is a reliable fortress for defending the fundamental interests of the revolution and the supreme interests of the state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Defending national sovereignty is the main task of the revolution and defending the country is connected with the fundamental interests of revolution, the supreme interests of the country. The military might of the country is the foremost national power in the struggle for independence and socialism against the imperialists and when the enemy is overpowered on the front of anti-imperialism and military affairs, victories can be won on all other fronts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the main front of the revolution also because the main key to victory in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation lies in increasing the military force. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Building a great prosperous powerful nation in the DPRK is a fierce class struggle against the U.S. imperialists and the enemies of revolution as well as a struggle to immensely increase overall potential of the country and thereby achieve the prosperity of the nation. The Korean People's Army is the main force here and success and failure in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation depend on its might. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a consistent stand of the Workers' Party of Korea to designate the front of anti-imperialism and military affairs as the main front of the Songun revolution. As long as there remains in the world imperialism whose mode of existence is aggression and looting, the army and people of the DPRK will keep a tight hold on the gun and always answer the tough policy of the U.S. imperialists with super toughness.

Spokesman for KPA Navy Command on S. Korean Military Authorities' Moves
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 14 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Navy Command of the Korean People's Army gave the following answer to a question put by KCNA Thursday as regards the south Korean military authorities' disturbing moves to dispatch more armed forces to waters close to the territorial waters of the north side in the West Sea of Korea under the pretext of intercepting Chinese fishing boats with the advent of blue crab picking season:
 The south Korean authorities recently said that they would forward-deploy warships belonging to the navy and the Maritime Police Office in waters north of the "fishery limit line" under the pretext of intercepting the illegal operation of Chinese fishing boats in the West Sea of Korea with the advent of the season, according to a radio report from south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are also considering staging joint naval exercises of the army and the police by mobilizing at least 10 warships and helicopters to operate in waters off the southern tip of Yongphyong Islet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They openly declared that they would dispatch more armed forces to the waters and stage joint naval exercises there although they are called "controversial waters" even by the world people as they are fraught with constant danger of armed clashes. This is, therefore, an outright challenge to the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No one can vouch that these disturbing military developments will not spark off a new West Sea skirmish as the south Korean authorities dared call for defending the "northern limit line." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year alone south Korean navy warships intruded into the territorial waters of the north side in the West Sea of Korea more than 40 times. Fortunately, no unpleasant incident occurred there entirely thanks to a high degree of self-restraint and patience on the part of the KPA servicemen who do not want the escalated tensions between the north and the south. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But there is a limit to their self-restraint and patience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities should stop their rash acts, pondering over what countermeasures will be taken by the north side when they recklessly dispatch warships and helicopters to the controversial waters, a hotbed of fresh military clashes.

Seminar on Kim Jong Il's Idea of Socialist Patriotism Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- A seminar of officials in the field of youth work on leader Kim Jong Il's idea of socialist patriotism was held here Thursday.
 Speakers explained and proved in depth the originality and great vitality of Kim Jong Il's idea of socialist patriotism, tasks before the organizations of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League to intensify the education in socialist patriotism among the young people as required by the Songun era and ways to carry them out and thus give a steady continuity to the tradition of the revolution and patriotism and eternally glorify the brilliant history and tradition of the Workers' Party of Korea and the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The core of socialist patriotism is intense loyalty to President   Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, the speakers said, adding that the devoted defence of the headquarters of the revolution represents the most ardent love for the socialist motherland and the most vivid expression of patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They noted that the Korean nation-first spirit serves as a fundamental source of giving full play to the spirit of socialist patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called for steadily intensifying the education in socialist patriotism among the young people and demonstrating to the full the resourcefulness and stamina of the young vanguard in the Songun era in their worthwhile struggle to build a great prosperous powerful nation so as to glorify the 21st century as Kim Jong Il's century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the seminar were officials concerned and officials and members of the youth league in Pyongyang.
